(1, 'Olympic National Park', 'Encompassing a staggering diversity of ecosystems, Olympic National Park is a natural wonderland that showcases the breadth of nature\'s beauty. From the lush Hoh Rainforest to the alpine peaks of the Olympic Mountains, the park offers an immersive experience for outdoor enthusiasts. Explore the pristine coastline, venture into old-growth forests, and embark on challenging hikes. Notable events include ranger-led programs, providing insights into the park\'s rich biodiversity, Native American history, and the ever-changing landscapes.', '3002 Mt Angeles Rd, Port Angeles, WA 98362', 'Phone: (360) 565-3130', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[{\"url\":\"https://olympicpeninsula.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/falls.jpg\",\"src\":\"Olympic Peninsula\"},{\"url\":\"https://npca.s3.amazonaws.com/images/15505/f6fb16ef-18c9-4577-98db-89d1b52207c4-banner.jpg?1639517402\",\"src\":\"National Parks Conservation Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a8/Cedar_Creek_Abbey_Island_Ruby_Beach.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/56abec0001dbae35f26b2da0/9cec3f33-d4de-4423-bb23-6431ae83bd40/Olympic-47.jpg?format=2500w\",\"src\":\"Big Brave Nomad\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.amtrakvacations.com/sites/amtrak/files/styles/hero/public/images/Olympic-National-Park.jpg?h=3a3df0c5&itok=4OshbrQJ\",\"src\":\"Amtrak Vacations\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Olympic National Park | America\'s National Parks\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NEMQdNYbBds?si=oZiC44u8nCzeD5WT\"},{\"title\":\"10 MUST VISIT Places in Olympic National Park | 51 Parks with the Newstates\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DJDvvw5KjjA?si=7CLEUONJz67mKOyH\"},{\"title\":\"Olympic National Park, Washington, USA [Amazing Places 4K]\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PHsR7KSQOX4?si=7dR2V3c1HJ3qMuzx\"}]'),
(2, 'Mount Rainier National Park', 'Dominated by the towering presence of Mount Rainier, this national park is a majestic landscape of glaciers, wildflower meadows, and dense forests. Mount Rainier National Park is a haven for hikers and nature lovers, offering a network of trails that lead to alpine vistas and cascading waterfalls. Beyond its natural splendors, the park holds cultural significance for Native American tribes. Notable events include the awe-inspiring wildflower bloom and ranger-led programs that delve into the geological and ecological wonders of the region.', '39000 State Route 706 E, Ashford, WA 98304', 'Phone: (360) 569-2211', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.usatoday.com/gcdn/-mm-/b9e0d0fb7a942a7df18baa51b58f8b1fac1a920e/c=0-92-1800-1109/local/-/media/2016/04/14/USATODAY/USATODAY/635962478654956950-MountRainierNPDannySeidman.jpg?width=1800&height=1017&fit=crop&format=pjpg&auto=webp\",\"src\":\"USA TODAY\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.worldtribune.org/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2022/03/Mt.Rainier_GettyImages-586164720.jpg\",\"src\":\"World Tribune\"},{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0a/2b/30/05/reflection-lake.jpg?w=2000&h=-1&s=1\",\"src\":\"Trip Advisor\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"An Amazing Day at Mount Rainier National Park | Three Classic Stops\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/q8uHS-auL1s?si=ewTL-R-MEYYl9SI9\"},{\"title\":\"24 Hours in Mount Rainier National Park: Hiking the Skyline Trail, Seeing 5 Waterfalls, & More\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bb9M81SUFQg?si=CMoir9zZSkV4heCN\"},{\"title\":\"Mt Rainier National Park In One Day (Paradise, Best Views & Day Hike)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xtOlKVkOnDo?si=imIdhSmsIF-rq-7s\"}]'),
(3, 'Hoh Rainforest', 'Within Olympic National Park, the Hoh Rainforest stands as a testament to the extraordinary biodiversity of the Pacific Northwest. With its towering trees, moss-draped branches, and pristine riverbanks, the Hoh Rainforest provides a magical immersion into a temperate rainforest ecosystem. Visitors can partake in guided nature walks, bird-watching excursions, and photography workshops to truly appreciate the enchanting beauty of this ancient and vibrant ecosystem.', '18113 Upper Hoh Rd, Forks, WA 98331', 'Phone: (360) 565-3131', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[{\"url\":\"https://olympicpeninsula.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/Hall-of-Mosses-Trail-Hoh-Rain-Forest-2.jpg\",\"src\":\"Olympic Peninsula\"},{\"url\":\"https://blog-assets.thedyrt.com/uploads/2019/04/shutterstock_93808600-1.jpg\",\"src\":\"The Dyrt\"},{\"url\":\"https://olympicpeninsula.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/WF-Trail-Willaby-Creek-Falls-3-Edited-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"Olympic Peninsula\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Hoh Rainforest Olympic National Park | Relaxation and Hiking Guide 4K\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/H2lwpCctjH4?si=3yuSzLAolwKlXFOW\"},{\"title\":\"How to See Olympic National Park in One Day | Hoh Rainforest\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9M27_K_yxCo?si=_F6_GdsQcAF5Apy3\"},{\"title\":\"Hoh Rainforest in Olympic National Park | Washington State, USA, Pacific Northwest\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/o1SFgWrO5fY?si=GCxz7v1dZ95vWP2O\"}]'),
(4, 'Steptoe Butte State Park', 'Offering sweeping panoramic views of the Palouse region, Steptoe Butte State Park is a captivating destination that provides a unique perspective on the surrounding landscape. The park is known for its iconic butte, which rises dramatically from the rolling hills. Visitors can drive to the summit for breathtaking vistas or explore the park\'s hiking trails. Steptoe Butte is particularly popular during the fall when the Palouse hills are ablaze with vibrant colors, creating a picturesque setting for photography enthusiasts.', 'Colfax, WA 99111', 'Phone: (509) 337-6457', '8:00 a.m. - Dusk', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0b/76/ad/c8/palouse-photo.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1\",\"src\":\"Tripadvisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/stateless-wspf-website/2019/05/5e18a984-steptoe-butte.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington State Parks Foundation\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.onlyinyourstate.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/GettyImages-499650369.jpg\",\"src\":\"OnlyInYourState\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Steptoe Butte State Park - Washington (4K HDR)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_Wpp5cTxaPA?si=ucM4mQaDfrTS-AX8\"},{\"title\":\"Beauty of Palouse WA - 4 Steptoe Butte State Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HVy-EdzrT8w?si=_iycROe2FAbJBhKf\"},{\"title\":\"4K (Ultra HD) Yellow Flowers - Spring Flowers at Steptoe Butte State Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/srVZe77sMhE?si=lbcFsIvO8yEbcg0j\"}]'),
(5, 'Deception Pass State Park', 'Encompassing scenic beauty and historical resonance, Deception Pass State Park is a captivating destination situated on Whidbey Island. The park offers a dramatic landscape with rugged cliffs, sandy beaches, and the iconic Deception Pass Bridge spanning turbulent waters. Beyond the natural beauty, the park holds cultural significance for Native American tribes and early European explorers. Visitors can explore the bridge, hike diverse trails, and engage in bird-watching activities. Deception Pass State Park stands as a multifaceted destination for nature enthusiasts, history buffs, and those seeking stunning coastal views.', '41229 State Rte 20, Oak Harbor, WA 98277', 'Phone: (360) 675-3767', '24 hours', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://whidbeycamanoislands.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/08/Deception-Pass-9435.jpg\",\"src\":\"Whidbey Island\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.cntraveler.com/photos/5f11d67c908df36068c50016/16:9/w_2560,c_limit/DeceptionPass-S342MM.jpg\",\"src\":\"Conde Nast Traveler\"},{\"url\":\"https://nickbotner.com/blog-images/WA_Deception-Pass/deception-pass-state-park-washington-1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Nick Botner\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Deception Pass State Park | Things to do | Most Visited State Park in Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wakBvVkx95M?si=31LGguMDeakD-r1q\"},{\"title\":\"Deception Pass State Park - Uncovering the 8 Best Spots | Day Trip from Seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/3z3lAadnR8o?si=eAl6s-Gl22lXSwTb\"},{\"title\":\"Deception Pass State Park | A Walking Tour\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wlyBKXVVwv8?si=4iz1bD2inzHb2ThR\"}]'),
(6, 'North Cascades National Park', 'Nestled in the northern reaches of Washington, North Cascades National Park boasts a rich history that echoes through its rugged mountains, alpine lakes, and dense forests. Home to Native American communities for thousands of years, the park\'s architectural simplicity lets the landscape speak for itself. Engage in ranger-led activities, from interpretive walks to educational programs, offering insights into the park\'s ecological significance.', '810 State Route 20\nSedro-Woolley, WA 98284', 'Phone: (360) 854-7200', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/Cascade_Pass_and_Pelton_Basin.jpg/1200px-Cascade_Pass_and_Pelton_Basin.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.audubon.org/north-cascades.jpg\",\"src\":\"National Auduon Society\"},{\"url\":\"https://s27363.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/09/Blue-Lake-Hike-North-Cascades.jpg.optimal.jpg\",\"src\":\"Earth Trekkers\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"North Cascades National Park, Washington, USA [Amazing Places 4K]\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/duGVGKvyKiI?si=vM0lVVSPy_gLa-yb\"},{\"title\":\"North Cascades National Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vmTvQeVZWo8?si=wSE99XLCNNFv2UXd\"},{\"title\":\"Best Things To Do In North Cascades National Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FoptSX6xZ9Y?si=xMcjI83ohhI4Pqxp\"}]'),
(7, 'Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument', 'Enshrined in the dramatic history of volcanic activity, Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument is a captivating testament to the power of nature\'s forces. The monument, established after the 1980 eruption, allows visitors to witness the profound changes to the landscape and the gradual process of recovery. Explore the Johnston Ridge Observatory for panoramic views, engage in educational programs detailing the eruption\'s impact, and embark on guided hikes to delve into the geological wonders of this living laboratory.', '3029 Spirit Lake Hwy, Castle Rock, WA 98611', 'Phone: (360) 449-7800', '8 AM-4 PM on weekdays, closed on weekends', 'Passes are $8 per adult (youth 15 and younger are free)', '[{\"url\":\"https://h2.gifposter.com/bingImages/MSHV_EN-US5482864526_1920x1080.jpg\",\"src\":\"Bing Wallpaper Gallery\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.scottsmorraphotography.com/images/xl/Mt-St-Helens-Summer-Sunrise-Wildflowers.jpg\",\"src\":\"Scott Smorra\"},{\"url\":\"https://kessiworld.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Kessiworld-MtStHelens2.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Kessi World\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument 4K Walk Tour!\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZVSLV7q-iXQ?si=R_zjvwWHHv8NFqGn\"},{\"title\":\"Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument (Epic Road Trip)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HlhaIfFwFqo?si=JV3LYdnKdgzOvBCw\"},{\"title\":\"Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument– WA State | Beautiful America Series – Episode#19\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/X6kBc7C973c?si=IQSwZzn9DkRTIKe2\"}]'),
(8, 'Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest', 'Spanning a vast expanse of diverse landscapes, Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest is a treasure trove for outdoor enthusiasts. From the towering peaks of Mount Baker to the lush forests and alpine meadows, the forest offers a rich tapestry of natural wonders. Engage in hiking, camping, and wildlife viewing amid the breathtaking scenery. Notable events include interpretive programs that shed light on the forest\'s ecological significance and its role as a haven for flora and fauna.', '1405 Emens Ave. N. Darrington, WA 98241', 'Phone: (425) 783-6000', 'Varies for location', '$5 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.mountaineers.org/volunteer/leader-resources/land-manager-resources/facilitated-access-permitting/mt-baker-snoqualmie-national-forest/@@images/bd7e291f-adaa-4d31-b947-7718b3d9f8e1.png\",\"src\":\"The Mountaineers\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.naturallyamazing.com/americasparks/2358.jpg\",\"src\":\"State Parks\"},{\"url\":\"https://sundarawestbnb.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/bigstock-Evening-At-Picture-Lake-With-M-354693854-1024x576.jpg\",\"src\":\"Sundara West B&B\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest | Full Episode\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QC2mrL5RK2k?si=knkjhRllI56XuKeX\"},{\"title\":\"Table Mountain Trail | Mt Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest | Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FTH4JsLY0zE?si=BXRffeFzWjlxHeFb\"},{\"title\":\"Experience ARTIST POINT PICTURE LAKE and BAGLEY LAKES | Mt Baker Snoqualmie\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BsU4MKQhsik?si=MVy6ITRh_LKuz6rd\"}]'),
(9, 'Lake Wenatchee State Park', 'Nestled against the picturesque backdrop of the Cascade Mountains, Lake Wenatchee State Park is a recreational haven for those seeking both water and mountain adventures. The park features a pristine lake, surrounded by dense forests and snow-capped peaks. Visitors can indulge in water activities, from kayaking to fishing, or explore the network of trails for hiking and bird watching. Seasonal events, such as winter sports during snowfall, add a dynamic touch to the park\'s offerings.', '21588 SR 207, Leavenworth, WA 98826', 'Phone: (509) 763-3101', '6:30 a.m. - Dusk', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/stateless-wspf-website/2019/05/2b46702a-lake-wenatchee.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington State Parks Foundation\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.yearofseattleparks.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/01/DSC_0074-1024x680.jpg\",\"src\":\"Year of Seattle Parks\"},{\"url\":\"https://hipcamp-res.cloudinary.com/image/upload/c_limit,f_auto,h_1200,q_60,w_1920/v1433543632/qzeoiob6wwieyu17a5lr.jpg\",\"src\":\"Hipcamp\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Lake Wenatchee State Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/l4Nnter2EJM?si=1A4XbHSXGzB9EThN\"},{\"title\":\"Explore Lake Wenatchee & Plain, WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/e-5A8EqEMAs?si=PP7UGNQwtVK4Ceyj\"},{\"title\":\"Lake Wenatchee State Park — Arrow Reviews\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-YpyTc21qeA?si=jkb8ab5GGzF6e06C\"}]'),
(10, 'Grove of the Patriarchs', 'Tucked within the enchanting embrace of Mount Rainier National Park, the Grove of the Patriarchs is a sanctuary of ancient trees. Towering Douglas firs and western red cedars create a cathedral-like atmosphere, transporting visitors back in time. The grove\'s minimalistic approach allows the natural majesty of these old-growth giants to shine. Engage in guided walks, exploring the ecological significance of this unique ecosystem, and discover the timeless beauty of these patriarchal trees.', 'Located just beyond the Stevens Canyon Entrance of the Mount Rainier National Park on Stevens Canyon Road', 'Phone: (360) 569-2211', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.utahsadventurefamily.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/08/Grove-of-the-Patriarchs-1.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Utah\'s Adventure Family\"},{\"url\":\"https://149799271.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Grove-of-the-Patriarchs-with-visitor.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Rainier\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/grove-of-the-patriarchs.jpg/@@download/image/Grove%20of%20the%20Patriarchs.%20Photo%20by%20HowtoJessWell.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Grove of the Patriarchs - Mt Rainier National Park 4K\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/f-ILfB_CHMY?si=hPDRNURrus7RBnhS\"},{\"title\":\"Grove of the Patriarchs - A Mt. Rainier National Park Adventure!\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/XwVOA8dhUH4?si=wCgy3c5E-ekP2dpg\"},{\"title\":\"Grove of The Patriarchs Trail - Mt Rainier National Park - Beautiful Old Growth Forest\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wm5Ux8Dchhw?si=4xCn8Oo_Dn3kZQKj\"}]'),
(11, 'Ruby Beach', 'Along the rugged coastline of Olympic National Park, Ruby Beach stands as a pristine and picturesque destination. The beach is adorned with sea stacks, tidal pools, and driftwood, creating a serene and photogenic coastal landscape. Visitors can explore sea caves, witness breathtaking sunsets, and experience the raw beauty of the Pacific Ocean. Ruby Beach is not just a destination; it\'s a sensory immersion into the untamed wonders of the Washington coast.', 'Located in the northernmost of the southern beaches in the coastal section of Olympic National Park', 'Phone: (360) 565-3130', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/06/f9/1b/bb/ruby-beach.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1\",\"src\":\"Tripadvisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/rubybeachhikingguide1.jpg/@@download/image/RubyBeachHikingGuide1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.themandagies.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Ruby-Beach-Washington-Coast-The-Mandagies-26-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"The Mandagies\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Ruby Beach Washington State 4K\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/25vH0lQR9dQ?si=Y0ylHnFNxNSo6bZp\"},{\"title\":\"Hiking Ruby Beach (Olympic National Park)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FwGn-lUAsnM?si=NF6rRXClIbyeUz0d\"},{\"title\":\"Possibly the Best Beach in Washington | Ruby Beach in Olympic National Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/NmaIx7ZsCU4?si=TMYRWj124xY9AC8q\"}]'),
(12, 'Long Beach', 'Stretching along the southwestern Washington coast, Long Beach is a captivating ribbon of sandy shores with a distinct Pacific Northwest charm. The expansive beach offers miles of coastline for beachcombing, kite flying, and enjoying the rhythmic sounds of the ocean. Notable events include the annual sandcastle building competition, where the beach transforms into an open-air gallery of intricate and imaginative sand sculptures. Long Beach is a quintessential coastal escape, inviting visitors to unwind and embrace the tranquility of the Pacific shore.', 'Long Beach, Washington 98631', 'Phone: (360) 449-7800', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/61eb640f60360a71b6ced4e7/af42f0e8-f4db-448c-bc0b-0526a8e4d931/IMG_3100.jpg\",\"src\":\"Pines and Vines\"},{\"url\":\"https://a.travel-assets.com/findyours-php/viewfinder/images/res70/493000/493846-long-beach-washington.jpg\",\"src\":\"Expedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://a.travel-assets.com/findyours-php/viewfinder/images/res70/493000/493847-long-beach-washington.jpg\",\"src\":\"Expedia\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Andy\'s Adventures: Exploring Long Beach, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/5G-XZwVGIjU?si=X1Q2Ht04jbTqG8t7\"},{\"title\":\"Long Beach WA 2016... 4K VIDEO\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JvyC-KxbX20?si=i9OtOlJdrGCmEPjy\"},{\"title\":\"SO MUCH TO DO! Where to go in Long Beach Washington | RV Travel\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/q5frJQ6MILw?si=HKFkwnm1RlFmIotX\"}]'),
(13, 'Second Beach', 'Tucked away in Olympic National Park, Second Beach beckons with its pristine beauty. Architectural features take a back seat to the natural wonders of sea stacks and tidal pools. Embark on a coastal hike, revel in the simplicity of beachcombing, and immerse yourself in the rhythmic sounds of the Pacific. No formal events are needed; nature\'s theater unfolds daily on this secluded shoreline.', 'Second Beach, WA', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/second-beack_mike-reid.jpg/@@images/8de9a2d9-10e5-4cfc-8eed-7315027c91bd.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/03/3a/7d/11/second-beach-trail.jpg?w=1200&h=1200&s=1\",\"src\":\"Trip Advisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/53af9a22e4b07a4f01183ebd/1459897117213-XLN7O5B9KZYPW3Y3WZ3U/Seastacks.jpg\",\"src\":\"Olympic Hiking Co.\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Second Beach, Olympic National Park, WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/3191cTKUKg0?si=ajZhEW07tPCBDUnD\"},{\"title\":\"Second Beach, Olympic National Park, La Push - Washington State\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/h9VvCEtttgQ?si=ODFdfBmOvQMy_rsS\"},{\"title\":\"backpacking vlog in olympic national park (second beach) | summer weekend diaries\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bwcT2gFy6MY?si=iZqyz_oSEfwvIgTN\"}]'),
(14, 'Shi Shi Beach', 'Accessible by a picturesque hike through the Olympic Peninsula, Shi Shi Beach unveils its natural allure without imposing structures. The coastal wilderness is the star, offering tidepool exploration, sea stack vistas, and a peaceful ambiance. Engage in self-guided walks, beach picnics, and take in the unspoiled beauty of this remote gem.', 'Shi Shi Beach Rd., Clallam Bay, WA 98326', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', '24 hours', '$15 Entrance Fee (Inside Olympic National Park)', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/trip-reports/2022/tripreport-image-2022-06-29-8632986478/@@download/image/PXL_20220628_172325320-.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.heraldnet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/10158974_web1_L1WallaceFalls-EDH-180119-1920x1280.jpg\",\"src\":\"Everett Herald\"},{\"url\":\"https://naturallyamazing.com/americasparks/20742.jpg\",\"src\":\"State Parks\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/point-of-arches.jpg-1/@@images/d6668a04-f489-4847-a5be-b08734e920d9.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://uprootedtraveler.com/wp-content/uploads/camping-at-shi-shi-beach-trail-shi-shi-beach-hike-9.jpg\",\"src\":\"Uprooted Traveler\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/53af9a22e4b07a4f01183ebd/1459897117213-XLN7O5B9KZYPW3Y3WZ3U/Seastacks.jpg\",\"src\":\"Olympic Hiking Co.\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Shi Shi Beach and Point of the Arches - Washington State\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/61Gj_AdfRC8?si=lLdA60fWLKMd1_7B\"},{\"title\":\"Backpacking Washington - Shi Shi Beach\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/c838YHOjRqw?si=dsV1-eqIT7sr0T3C\"},{\"title\":\"John\'s Northwest Adventures - Shi Shi Beach Point of the Arches\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/_eSdeobthKE?si=dA2z-qCaRHczWqjf\"}]'),
(15, 'Wallace Falls', 'Nestled in the lush surroundings of Wallace Falls State Park, the falls themselves take center stage without the need for elaborate architecture. A series of cascading waterfalls set against a backdrop of evergreen forests, the area is a haven for hikers and nature enthusiasts. Explore the trails, revel in the soothing sounds of rushing water, and participate in ranger-led hikes highlighting the park\'s biodiversity.', '14503 Wallace Lake Road, Gold Bar, WA 98251', 'Phone: (360) 793-0420', '6:30 AM - 5 PM', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/trip-reports/2022/tripreport-image-2022-06-29-8632986478/@@download/image/PXL_20220628_172325320-.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.heraldnet.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/10158974_web1_L1WallaceFalls-EDH-180119-1920x1280.jpg\",\"src\":\"Everett Herald\"},{\"url\":\"https://naturallyamazing.com/americasparks/20742.jpg\",\"src\":\"State Parks\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Wallace Falls State Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vK0A8v_YgkY?si=1SPYMTpm2yS6yn9n\"},{\"title\":\"Hiking Wallace Falls - Ultimate Guide to One of the Most Beloved\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ILH7bYq8NyU?si=cEBOnKUCcMt2Sob3\"},{\"title\":\"Hiking Washington - Wallace Falls\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/t3g2qyykZd4?si=uyqGeVzgqxcWY9uc\"}]'),
(16, 'Nooksack Falls', 'Set within the scenic splendor of the Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest, Nooksack Falls showcases nature\'s artistry without human-made structures. The falls cascade dramatically over rugged cliffs, creating a breathtaking spectacle. Explore nearby trails, listen to the roaring water, and enjoy the simplicity of this natural attraction.', 'Mt Baker Hwy Nf-33. Glacier, WA 98244', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/hike-image-2020-06-08-2915624787/@@images/a6232678-2699-4ed3-a31d-c10ac5825618.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Nooksack Falls like you\'ve never seen! (...from a drone)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EXf_Duop37o?si=eCe2XaLB3-1cxR4W\"},{\"title\":\"Frozen Waterfall - Nooksack Falls - Mt. Baker - WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8T2w0DFxDrI?si=02-wokPAMJWPL6QV\"},{\"title\":\"Magnificent Nooksack Falls - Calming Sounds of Crashing Water - Nooksack Falls - Short\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/jfBkvfhhmQo?si=JeOHJfQiXQ1HHZYv\"}]'),
(17, 'Snoqualmie Falls', 'Carving its way through the Snoqualmie River, Snoqualmie Falls is a majestic natural wonder surrounded by lush landscapes. The falls themselves provide a captivating display without requiring architectural embellishments. Enjoy viewpoints, scenic overlooks, and the soothing ambiance of the cascading water. Periodic cultural events and festivals celebrate the falls\' significance in the region\'s history.', '6501 Railroad Ave SE Snoqualmie, Washington, 98024', 'Phone: (425) 326-2563', 'From sun up to sun down', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/20/Snoqualmie_Falls%2C_Snoqualmie%2C_WA.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://s39023.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Fall-Colors-Snoqualmie-Falls.jpg.optimal.jpg\",\"src\":\"Where Are Those Morgans\"},{\"url\":\"https://assets.simpleviewinc.com/simpleview/image/upload/c_limit,q_75,w_1200/v1/crm/bellevue/210-3-0744_jpeg-daaa849c5056a36_daab32cc-5056-a36a-0bf7b70a116f6950.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Bellevue Washington\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Visit Snoqualmie Falls\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/lY5LZUL_IgI?si=y9Y1G3m1U658VU9R\"},{\"title\":\"Snoqualmie Falls Trail Walking Tour\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/c4evMoR1vNk?si=mFeGeTeZImceFoRh\"},{\"title\":\"Snoqualmie Falls and Seattle Winery Tour from Seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/UG0hrB2kYSs?si=VHSZtJuCf-BiBnjb\"}]'),
(18, 'Palouse Falls State Park', 'Tucked away in the heart of the Palouse region, Palouse Falls State Park is a testament to natural beauty with its cascading waterfalls. Architectural features take a back seat to the dramatic landscape, offering breathtaking viewpoints and hiking trails. Explore the rugged terrain, witness the falls\' power, and partake in stargazing events, highlighting the park\'s nocturnal charm.', 'Palouse Falls Rd, LaCrosse, WA 99143', 'Phone: (509) 646-9218', 'Summer: 6:30 a.m. - Dusk\nWinter: 8 a.m. - Dusk', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.tripsavvy.com/thmb/GoWKhwfhI1zM8LsCQ6MgSzDBDRg=/2120x1414/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/GettyImages-182110697-5b5558c346e0fb003701b6a2.jpg\",\"src\":\"TripSavvy\"},{\"url\":\"https://washingtonisforadventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/palouse-falls-state-park.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington is for Adventure\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Palouse Falls State Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ow2YQ1IfNc0?si=Debsn3YDGIpneayN\"},{\"title\":\"A GIANT Waterfall | Palouse Falls & Eastern vs. Western Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oKWdDGwOvvQ?si=BsWdPtIms2CVIJ4I\"},{\"title\":\"Palouse Falls: Best of Washington Documentary Short [4K]\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bVJyYqtlEhI?si=lc23-reQSt8rbBxP\"}]'),
(19, 'Franklin Falls', 'Cradled within the Snoqualmie Pass, Franklin Falls captivates with its simplicity and accessibility. The falls themselves are the focal point, requiring no architectural embellishments. Hike through evergreen forests to reach this enchanting cascade, where the calming sounds of rushing water create a serene atmosphere. The falls\' surroundings offer ideal conditions for nature walks and photography.', 'Franklin Falls, WA 98045', 'Phone: (425) 888-1421', '  ', '$5 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/trip-reports/2021/tripreport-image-2021-12-31-9804321863/@@download/image/Franklin%20Falls%20Close.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/0c/c3/9d/e1/fb-img-1472578625696.jpg?w=1200&h=1200&s=1\",\"src\":\"Tripadvisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.thenewstribune.com/outdoors/rz5ph2/picture132237509/alternates/FREE_1140/Franklin2\",\"src\":\"The News Tribune\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"FRANKLIN FALLS - Easy Hike Just 50 Minutes East of Seattle | EXPLORE WASHINGTON\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ow2YQ1IfNc0?si=Debsn3YDGIpneayN\"},{\"title\":\"Franklin Falls WA -- Merry Christmas & Happy New Year 4K UHD\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/eCM4lSAc7N8?si=wvsOIXKzzC4Rttle\"},{\"title\":\"Franklin Falls, Washington - Best Washington Winter Hikes Near Seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/yw7iA9D1qjM?si=3soNVLGcN8Z-JJVE\"}]'),
(20, 'Guler Ice Caves', 'Nestled in the Gifford Pinchot National Forest, the Guler Ice Caves present a unique natural phenomenon without the need for human-made structures. Venture into the caves to witness the surreal beauty of ice formations. Engage in self-guided exploration, appreciating the caves\' geological wonders and the tranquility of this remote icy realm.', 'Trout Lake, WA 98650', 'Phone: (509) 395-3402', '24 hours', '$5 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.oregonhikers.org/w/images/thumb/6/61/Inside_The_Tube%2C_Guler_Ice_Cave.jpg/400px-Inside_The_Tube%2C_Guler_Ice_Cave.jpg\",\"src\":\"Oregon Hikers\"},{\"url\":\"https://hawkinwinter.com//wp-content/uploads/2012/06/trout-lake-caves-17.jpg\",\"src\":\"Hawk in Winter\"},{\"url\":\"https://atlas-assets.roadtrippers.com/uploads/place_image/image/56214822/-strip_-quality_60_-interlace_Plane_-resize_640x360_U__-gravity_center_-extent_640x360/place_image-image-e90ab506-8e61-465a-bf3a-e8b6e19ed184.jpg\",\"src\":\"Roadtrippers Map\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Ice Cave in SUMMER! Guler Ice Caves\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/k9rf5BF2W2M?si=oPLUkEvo1R1VOjqQ\"},{\"title\":\"Guler Ice Cave\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QaUGgQRgUag?si=uT-OIlWnUC4ZKTZt\"},{\"title\":\"Guler Ice Caves\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/91D3-bVNXPU?si=LGVX0TpC231j3Fvk\"}]'),
(21, 'Ape Cave', 'Carved by volcanic activity near Mount St. Helens, Ape Cave stands as a subterranean wonder. The cave\'s geological features, shaped by lava flows, provide an otherworldly experience without the need for architectural enhancements. Embark on a spelunking adventure, navigating the dark passages and marveling at the cave\'s unique formations. Ranger-led programs add educational depth to this volcanic wonder.', 'Ape Cave, WA 98616', 'Phone: (360) 449-7800', '   ', '$5 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.fs.usda.gov/Internet/FSE_MEDIA/fseprd899277.jpg\",\"src\":\"USDA Forest Service\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/trip-reports/2023/tripreport-image-2023-06-11-0171976950/@@images/1e7ff1f8-011d-4651-b936-f232e8069bc8.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://sealegadventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/PXL_20230805_230433661.PORTRAIT.ORIGINAL_Original-scaled.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Sea Leg Adventure\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Ape Cave: the longest known lava tube in North America | Let\'s Get Out There\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ynAajsaRwOs?si=uFVGZSEdMygXSClo\"},{\"title\":\"Upper Ape Cave - Mount St Helens National Volcanic Monument\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Lrm5ydlNDiA?si=1GxE2elHJg4NJai4\"},{\"title\":\"Ape Cave | Nick on the Rocks\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Uks7Fq67YOk?si=tRxi-zYD9n-xF1fR\"}]'),
(22, 'Chihuly Garden and Glass', 'Located in the heart of Seattle, Chihuly Garden and Glass seamlessly blends art with nature. The architectural features of the exhibition enhance the presentation of Dale Chihuly\'s glass masterpieces. Wander through the garden, marvel at the intricate glass sculptures, and engage in periodic artist talks and glassblowing demonstrations, providing a dynamic and immersive artistic experience.', '305 Harrison St, Seattle, WA 98109', 'Phone: (206) 753-4940', '10 AM - 5 PM\n10 AM - 6 PM (F-Sat)', 'Varies from Free - $35', '[{\"url\":\"https://d3qvqlc701gzhm.cloudfront.net/full/ef1f75819b0a72d8372b68d40c1500bbade0898d938a957da6b827afdc04e900.jpg\",\"src\":\"CityPass\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.chihulygardenandglass.com/img/_1200x630_crop_center-center_82_none/03_exhibtion_rotator_05.jpg?mtime=1620077151\",\"src\":\"Chihuly Garden and Glass\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.cntraveler.com/photos/5fc57d37013df4de80687aff/16:9/w_2560,c_limit/Glasshouse%20Sculpture.jpg\",\"src\":\"Conde Nast Traveler\"},{\"url\":\"https://1.bp.blogspot.com/-xheUshKXVks/UJ3dasNHtdI/AAAAAAAABDQ/15vq0cNGI9Q/s1600/gardenofglass.jpg\",\"src\":\"Artscapes\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.chihuly.com/sites/default/files/images/CGG_SpringBloom_2_0675_TR.jpg\",\"src\":\"Chihuly\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Chihuly Garden and Glass Exhibit in Seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/LfAkCTlC2F0?si=bsTH4Jxj6e0x9U4l\"},{\"title\":\"Chihuly Garden and Glass\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rPZSZFC3YJw?si=cY5SyfU3x7JgVEg3\"},{\"title\":\"Chihuly Garden and Glass seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FSH3qsD4fdo?si=KekkODRQSbJeJWNe\"}]'),
(23, 'Musuem of Pop Culture (MoPOP)', 'Situated at the Seattle Center, the Museum of Pop Culture (MoPOP) immerses visitors in the world of popular culture. Architecturally striking, the building itself is a work of art designed by Frank Gehry. Inside, explore exhibitions on music, science fiction, and gaming. Attend live events, film screenings, and interactive displays, seamlessly blending architectural aesthetics with the celebration of pop culture.', '325 5th Ave N, Seattle, WA 98109', 'Phone: (206) 770-2700', 'Thurs–Tues: 10:00am–5:00pm\nClosed on Wednesdays', 'Varies ($25+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://d3qvqlc701gzhm.cloudfront.net/full/ef1f75819b0a72d8372b68d40c1500bbade0898d938a957da6b827afdc04e900.jpg\",\"src\":\"CityPass\"},{\"url\":\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTuSxbwmp4LkubIs0vnzny4tl8zirpw-qXMZCPYh2whjn6vmJMH0G4M9tJuUDx3W7oEsEM&usqp=CAU\",\"src\":\"MoPOP\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.cntraveler.com/photos/5afb519274903712462193e5/16:9/w_2560,c_limit/Museum-of-Pop-Culture_2018_BuildingExterior.jpg\",\"src\":\"Conde Nast Traveler\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.mopop.org/media/2297/30975369866_09eb9c61c2_o.jpg\",\"src\":\"MoPOP\"},{\"url\":\"https://lp-cms-production.s3.amazonaws.com/public/2021-05/shutterstockRF_1446549995.jpg\",\"src\":\"Lonely Planet\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Museum of Pop Culture - MoPop - Seattle, WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/b1M-Zkf39wM?si=JS0exQrfJ30Uf5sb\"},{\"title\":\"Inside The MoPop & Going Up To Top Of Seattle Space Needle - Museum Of Pop Culture is Incredible\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JSKCcTRGlDk?si=nmVDtXaMVsaWv0bs\"},{\"title\":\"MUSEUM OF POP CULTURE SEATTLE (MoPOP)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I2w6bJkHgBU?si=OtJobSmhWHdI1EL9\"}]'),
(24, 'Washington State History Museum', 'Anchoring Tacoma\'s historic district, the Washington State History Museum seamlessly integrates architectural elegance with historical exploration. Traverse through time within the museum\'s exhibits, showcasing the state\'s diverse history. Participate in curator-led tours, educational workshops, and community events that bridge the architectural and historical aspects of this cultural hub.', '1911 Pacific Ave, Tacoma, WA 98402', 'Phone: (253) 272-3500', 'Tuesday-Sunday: 10:00 AM-5:00 PM', 'Varies from Free - $14', '[{\"url\":\"https://img.locationscout.net/images/2019-12/tacoma-history-museum-usa_l.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Hotcore\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.creoexhibits.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/WAState-History-10.jpg\",\"src\":\"Creo\"},{\"url\":\"https://woed.com/wp-content/uploads/WSHM_Featured-Image-2000x1330.jpg\",\"src\":\"West Office\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Take a Look Tacoma -- Washington State History Museum\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/21W_6w3m3Lc?si=0MHjOQJE96X59SWH\"},{\"title\":\"My Favorite Places - Model Railroad Exhibit at the WA State History Museum\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xRqf6x3k3oI?si=96anxVGXJIOqC5Sw\"},{\"title\":\"Washington State History Museum, Downtown Tacoma, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/MMTjEvDnyNM?si=3Ws3qItQ5QuGWBnx\"}]'),
(25, 'The Museum of Flight', 'Located near Boeing Field in Seattle, The Museum of Flight is a tribute to aviation history. Architecturally designed to showcase aeronautical wonders, the museum features iconic aircraft, spacecraft, and interactive exhibits. Immerse yourself in aviation history through guided tours, flight simulations, and periodic aviation-themed events, blending architectural aesthetics with the captivating stories of flight.', '9404 E Marginal Way S, Seattle, WA 98108', 'Phone: (206) 764-5700', '10:00 AM to 5:00 PM', 'Varies from Free - $26', '[{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/1a/42/87/cc/the-aviation-pavilion.jpg?w=1200&h=-1&s=1\",\"src\":\"Tripadvisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.tacdn.com/media/attractions-splice-spp-674x446/06/67/ae/c9.jpg\",\"src\":\"Viator\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.cnet.com/a/img/resize/2f78e8d1489d2c98ea4e39acb185edd8c69c52ad/hub/2019/02/28/bba7768a-4bdc-4c33-98df-133c0d630497/museum-of-flight-10-of-1.jpg?auto=webp&fit=crop&height=675&width=1200\",\"src\":\"CNET\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Seattle Museum of Flight, Narrated Tour - Boeing Field, Seattle, Washington USA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/c6e075X8hfQ?si=mR5UA7P07kAQ9SFU\"},{\"title\":\"The Museum of Flight Tour\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/EWFHryWA2fw?si=ilbl_c3zIf6FRMzu\"},{\"title\":\"Seattle\'s Museum of Flight | Travel Channel\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/CV0o2y4-r5g?si=ZwvLJan4L-MN6aBn\"}]'),
(26, 'Bainbridge Island Museum of Art', '', '550 Winslow Way E, Bainbridge Island, WA 98110', 'Phone: (206) 842-4451', '10 AM - 5 PM', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://d3qvqlc701gzhm.cloudfront.net/full/ef1f75819b0a72d8372b68d40c1500bbade0898d938a957da6b827afdc04e900.jpg\",\"src\":\"CityPass\"},{\"url\":\"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTuSxbwmp4LkubIs0vnzny4tl8zirpw-qXMZCPYh2whjn6vmJMH0G4M9tJuUDx3W7oEsEM&usqp=CAU\",\"src\":\"MoPOP\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.biartmuseum.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/Visit-Exterior-1920x875.jpg\",\"src\":\"Bainbridge Island Museum of Art\"},{\"url\":\"https://cdnassets.hw.net/a3/d3/1668ea954167a8ff2ae0c1a7e7f2/d76b0fa08ce54f32829fa4290ccd4cf8.jpg\",\"src\":\"Architect Magazine\"},{\"url\":\"https://coatesdesign.com/wp-content/uploads/OurWork_Civic_BIMA_6-1280x820.jpg\",\"src\":\"Coates Design Architects\"},{\"url\":\"https://a.travel-assets.com/findyours-php/viewfinder/images/res70/493000/493017-bainbridge-island-museum-of-art.jpg\",\"src\":\"Expedia\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Introducing the Bainbridge Island Museum of Art\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9sFBQ6SFHkU?si=qgDLUrpAP4-XxheC\"}]'),
(27, 'Fort Vancouver National Historic Site', 'Enriched with historical significance, Fort Vancouver National Historic Site serves as a portal to the region\'s past. Established as a fur trading post in the 19th century, the fort played a pivotal role in the region\'s development. Explore reconstructed buildings, engage in living history demonstrations, and discover the layers of cultural exchange that shaped the Pacific Northwest. Periodic events include reenactments and educational programs, offering a vibrant journey into the area\'s colonial history.', '612 E Reserve St, Vancouver, WA 98661', 'Phone: (253) 272-3500', 'Tuesday-Sunday:  9 AM - 4 PM', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://res.cloudinary.com/simpleview/image/upload/v1659627916/clients/vancouverusa/068_DSC_5869_small_Copy_ee0df8e8-a271-4a60-b563-6b314c59051d.jpg\",\"src\":\"Vancouver, WA\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.nps.gov/common/uploads/banner_image/pwr/homepage/CB3CF57E-1DD8-B71B-0B69381E816B74B0.jpg\",\"src\":\"National Park Service\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.nps.gov/fova/learn/news/images/Fort-Vancouver-Garden.jpg?maxwidth=1300&maxheight=1300&autorotate=false\",\"src\":\"National Park Service\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Fort Vancouver: A Historic Gem | HISTORY\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ttwnzHoVgLE?si=45acg7ROxo4OBKrX\"},{\"title\":\"Vancouver USA Originals—Fort Vancouver\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/XmYG-f7O3F0?si=xRTIT9pCpqQw8fJs\"},{\"title\":\"Fort Vancouver National Historic Site Washington Sightseeing\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/5s6Gr2JKQvU?si=JK_V5UjivGqd3c-u\"}]'),
(28, 'Pioneer Square', 'Pioneer Square stands as a vibrant district in Seattle, embodying the city\'s rich history and artistic spirit. Cobblestone streets and historic storefronts set the scene for a dynamic neighborhood. Delve into the district\'s past through underground tours, showcasing Seattle\'s evolution. Art galleries, street performances, and eclectic boutiques add a contemporary flair, making Pioneer Square a cultural hub where history seamlessly intertwines with modern creativity.', 'Pioneer Square, Seattle, WA', 'Phone: (206) 667-0687\nEmail: info@pioneersquare.org', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/nooklyn-pro/neighborhoods/225/wide/occidental_square_-_photo_by_olivia_brent_crop.jpg?1597168590\",\"src\":\"Nooklyn\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.travelingwithmj.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/08/Depositphotos_133018822_l-2015.jpg\",\"src\":\"Traveling with MJ\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.seattleandsound.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/pioneersquare.jpg\",\"src\":\"Seattle and Sound\"},{\"url\":\"https://d3mqmy22owj503.cloudfront.net/05/500005/images/poi/pioneer-square/200-scenic-washington-best-historic-districts-in-seattle--pioneer-square-1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Scenic Washington State\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Seattle, Washington | PIONEER SQUARE | 4K Walking Tour\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/8U9PD6qvpRw?si=RK0SeVAVuANx7k8J\"},{\"title\":\"Exploring Seattle - Exploring Pioneer Square | Seattle, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PHcX5JauN5o?si=JdOk34BjJ_ir2Z79\"},{\"title\":\"Downtown Seattle Walking Adventure | Pioneer Square | Pike\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QMZBmmv1EwA?si=MFJ8xMrCNPc3pTve\"}]'),
(29, 'Fort Casey State Park', 'Nestled on Whidbey Island, Fort Casey State Park beckons with its maritime history and scenic beauty. The park features historical military structures, including coastal defense batteries, offering glimpses into the area\'s strategic significance. Beyond history, the park provides panoramic views of Puget Sound, making it an ideal spot for picnics, beachcombing, and wildlife observation.', '1280 Engle Road, Coupeville, WA 98239', 'Phone: (206) 770-2700', '8am – Dusk', 'Entrance Fees: Varies ($10+)', '[{\"url\":\"https://storage.googleapis.com/stateless-wspf-website/2019/05/8edd6c19-fort-casey.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington State Parks Foundation\"},{\"url\":\"https://washingtonisforadventure.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/fort-casey-state-park-trails-and-beach-1024x683.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington is for Adventure\"},{\"url\":\"https://tripsaroundme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/20220424_151527-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"Trips Around Me\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Ep. 318: Fort Casey, Washington | Puget Sound RV travel camping history Whidbey Island\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wbo-MD4iplg?si=JSVXFo3bhMeJHeXx\"},{\"title\":\"Brief History of Fort Casey on Whidbey Island, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/LHB_JgaprpU?si=pc3cFLMAgqZX7jET\"},{\"title\":\"What To Do On WHIDBEY ISLAND? Fort Casey, Price Sculpture Forest, Deception Pass & More\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/21OPDR_lbC0?si=iG7fkXU--M-NnE1X\"}]'),
(30, 'Manresa Castle', 'Perched atop a hill in Port Townsend, Manresa Castle is not only a historic structure but also an inviting retreat. Built in the late 19th century, the castle exudes old-world charm. Today, it serves as a hotel where guests can experience a blend of history and hospitality. Explore the castle\'s unique architecture, dine in its historic dining room, and immerse yourself in the castle\'s rumored paranormal activity.', '651 Cleveland St, Port Townsend, WA 98368', 'Phone: (360) 385-5750\nEmail: info@manresacastle.com', '24 hours', 'Rates vary ', '[{\"url\":\"https://static.wixstatic.com/media/cd57c5_36ff91bf3f1c45c981b78380ffdb52a4~mv2.jpg/v1/fit/w_2500,h_1330,al_c/cd57c5_36ff91bf3f1c45c981b78380ffdb52a4~mv2.jpg\",\"src\":\"Manresa Castle\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.washington-coast-adventures.com/images/edwardian-cocktail-lounge-manresa-castle.jpg\",\"src\":\"Washington Coast Adventures\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"#3 \'23 - \\\"Haunting\\\" Manresa Castle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/x5B5X6yx7HA?si=MgTWCJoveG48bYw-\"},{\"title\":\"The Manresa Castle Hotel\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/pG2woECpf3g?si=lm2n9Z-g9zrb4wp5\"},{\"title\":\"Tour - Manresa Castle Investigation (Port Townsend, WA) - The Castle & Grounds\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-IZtlLedv9I?si=A_XiaAXAaSD_E5wy\"}]'),
(31, 'Roslyn Historic District', 'The Roslyn Historic District transports visitors to a bygone era, steeped in the history of coal mining and cultural diversity. Famous as the filming location for the television series \"Northern Exposure,\" the district boasts well-preserved buildings and a tight-knit community. Wander through charming streets, visit historic storefronts, and absorb the district\'s small-town charm. Periodic events celebrate the town\'s heritage, creating a welcoming atmosphere for exploration.', 'Roslyn, WA', '   ', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3b/Shops_in_downtown_Roslyn%2C_NY.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/03/20/realestate/20LIVING-slide-ZDJ0/20LIVING-slide-ZDJ0-articleLarge.jpg?quality=75&auto=webp&disable=upscale\",\"src\":\"The New York Times\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.hmdb.org/Photos5/597/Photo597303.jpg?7132021102600PM\",\"src\":\"The Historical Marker Database\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Roslyn WA * Movies * TV * and Coal Miners\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/s5deDlog9Bw?si=M6zQvEqr1BBfHpud\"}]'),
(32, 'Marmes Rockshelter', 'Situated along the Palouse River, the Marmes Rockshelter is an archaeological treasure trove, offering insights into the prehistoric cultures of the region. The site contains evidence of ancient human habitation, including tools and artifacts. While not physically accessible to the public to preserve its integrity, interpretive centers and educational programs provide a window into the fascinating history unearthed at Marmes Rockshelter.', 'Marmes Rockshelter, WA 99143', '   ', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://images.seattletimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/112217-MarmesPacific_Lead.jpg?d=780x386\",\"src\":\"The Seattle Times\"},{\"url\":\"https://s3.wp.wsu.edu/uploads/sites/1883/2018/05/45FR50.20500.jpg\",\"src\":\"Museum of Anthropology\"},{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2c/Officials_at_Marmes_Rockshelter.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Marmes Rockshelter , WA ~ The Dam & 12,000+ Years Of Lost History\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/anIPlrQuCZ4?si=sy8qtAXpzUD51r4L\"}]'),
(33, 'Hanford Reach National Monument', 'Along the Columbia River, Hanford Reach National Monument stands as a vast, protected area preserving diverse ecosystems and cultural resources. Once part of the Manhattan Project, the monument now serves as a haven for wildlife and a testament to environmental restoration. Explore the monument through guided tours, birdwatching, and hiking, appreciating the natural and historical tapestry of this unique landscape.', 'Mattawa, WA 99349', 'Phone: (509) 546-8300', 'sunrise to sunset', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://wa.audubon.org/sites/default/files/styles/hero_mobile/public/editorial-card-images/static_page/whitebluffswilderness_en-us12259474431_1366x768.jpg?itok=KRPlXlrN\",\"src\":\"Audubon Washington\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.fws.gov/sites/default/files/styles/extra_medium_square/public/banner_images/2021-08/White%20Bluffs_2.jpg?itok=BH0BAntA\",\"src\":\"U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5602e09be4b053956b5c8d3a/1497385099544-IXOTSUZDXUX4C65S3CGJ/tncwashington_40648503.jpg?format=2500w\",\"src\":\"The Nature Conservancy in Washington\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"WHITE BLUFFS [North Slope] - Hanford Reach National Monument, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/9HSt0Jmye6k?si=SiZEjftrLxJyg54A\"},{\"title\":\"Hanford Reach (White Bluffs) History\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/rLfQ-__pmyE?si=099EvV2SGdmZ_B54\"},{\"title\":\"The White Bluffs at Hanford Reach - Columbia River Free Flowing Stretch\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/0iyM04F4exs?si=G1-vAD5sOQ-3yU-U\"}]');
