(34, 'The Enchantments', 'Tucked within the Alpine Lakes Wilderness, The Enchantments is a pristine alpine wonderland. Known for its crystal-clear lakes, rugged peaks, and enchanting landscapes, this destination is a haven for hikers and outdoor enthusiasts. Permits are required for overnight stays, allowing visitors to immerse themselves in the breathtaking scenery. From epic hikes to serene moments by alpine lakes, The Enchantments offer a transcendent experience in the heart of Washington\'s wilderness.', 'Leavenworth, WA 98826', 'Phone: (509) 548-2550', '24 hours', '$5 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a7/Prusik_Peak.JPG\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://miro.medium.com/v2/resize:fit:1400/1*2HgLFgSHGmmSQFgNszz6OA.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Medium\"},{\"url\":\"https://res.cloudinary.com/sagacity/image/upload/c_crop,h_994,w_1500,x_0,y_0/c_limit,dpr_auto,f_auto,fl_lossy,q_80,w_1080/Enchantments_MaggieCheng_stiykg.jpg\",\"src\":\"Seattle Met\"},{\"url\":\"https://wherewewentnext.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/08/CrystalLake-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"Where We Went Next\"},{\"url\":\"https://s27363.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/How-to-Hike-the-Enchantments.jpg.optimal.jpg\",\"src\":\"Earth Trekkers\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"THE ENCHANTMENTS HIKE, WASHINGTON | Complete Day Hiking Guide\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/aVarwhCwjzI?si=MzsLR2NOLP9lHAXr\"},{\"title\":\"Hiking For 15 Hours Straight | The Enchantments, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/M00FImh8os0?si=gEAHWXg-LNxh7ejC\"},{\"title\":\"Washington - Enchantments - Canon 5D Mark II - Glidecam HD 4000 | DEVINSUPERTRAMP\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-sBnepbX1rY?si=2DjlIGUq2mnV7vwY\"},{\"title\":\"Day Hiking the Enchantments\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/LC5355BWIBE?si=jhxCQY_KCC-wR1lU\"}]'),
(35, 'Mount Si', 'Dominating the skyline near North Bend, Mount Si offers a challenging yet rewarding hiking experience. Popular among outdoor enthusiasts, the trail ascends through lush forests, eventually revealing panoramic views of the surrounding landscape. Hikers can witness diverse flora and fauna along the way, with the summit providing a stunning vantage point of the Cascade Range.', 'Mt Si, WA 98045', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', '24 hours', '$10 Entrance Fee', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/15148635572_d7cb258404_o.jpg/@@images/15c087f2-9b6f-4573-ab13-68fc5bd80a97.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.mountaineers.org/activities/routes-places/mount-si-main-trail/@@images/image\",\"src\":\"The Mountaineers\"},{\"url\":\"https://photos.thetrek.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/31152442/zy-photo-2019-07-14-00000118_original.jpg\",\"src\":\"The Trek\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Hiking Washington - Mount Si\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZmeMlT6TQPI?si=jw3TnwwvsxcmSpa4\"},{\"title\":\"Here\'s Why Mount Si Stands Out in TV History\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/cNqhS9nMs3E?si=t67i-K3c_ifMjlzU\"},{\"title\":\"HOW TO TRAIN FOR HIKING & BACKPACKING | Go Hiking | Mount Si\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6vFKJe1YwXo?si=XIKy2BoRbkYTf2iY\"}]'),
(36, 'Rattlesnake Ledge', 'A favorite among hikers, Rattlesnake Ledge showcases the beauty of the Pacific Northwest with a relatively short and accessible trail. The hike culminates at a rocky outcrop, offering sweeping views of Rattlesnake Lake and the Snoqualmie Valley. It\'s an ideal spot for a day hike, photography, and enjoying the serenity of the surrounding wilderness.', 'North Bend, WA 98045', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://kuow-prod.imgix.net/store/f7aa94bc37b69c20c9633da4f39afae0.jpg\",\"src\":\"KUOW\"},{\"url\":\"https://i0.wp.com/oliviamichelleh.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/IMG_4213.jpg?resize=960%2C720&ssl=1\",\"src\":\"Olivia Michelle\"},{\"url\":\"https://mtsgreenway.org/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/RattlesnakeLedge_KatieEgresi_032321-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"Mountains to Sound Greenway\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"RATTLESNAKE LEDGE | The Ginger Runner Adventure Club\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vTP0D_UapQk?si=G88S4e2z4QYAF_pC\"},{\"title\":\"Rattlesnake Ledge: North Bend, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IeHvb5euU5Y?si=Cg8TD7zl6qXVrVtC\"},{\"title\":\"Rattlesnake Ledge || North Bend, Washington State\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oYA0pldVCv0?si=C4Aq9tBnojShoRcc\"}]'),
(37, 'Lena Lake Trail', 'Nestled in Olympic National Forest, the Lena Lake Trail invites hikers to explore the lush, old-growth forest leading to the pristine Lena Lake. The trail features diverse plant life and occasional wildlife sightings. Once at the lake, visitors can enjoy a peaceful retreat, with opportunities for camping, fishing, and immersing themselves in the natural tranquility.', 'N Hamma Hamma Rd, Hoodsport, WA 98548', 'Phone: (360) 765 2200', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/upper-lena-lake-by-bill.jpeg/@@download/image/Upper%20Lena%20Lake%20by%20Bill.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.wta.org/site_images/hikes/lena-lake-by-gt123.jpeg/@@download/image/Lena%20Lake.%20Photo%20by%20rutcat.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Washington Trails Association\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Solo Backpacking to the Loneliest Lake in Olympic National Park!\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qcICVhPCTqU?si=yxxgxgamsQxXYo8Y\"},{\"title\":\"Hiking Lena Lake (Olympic Mountains)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/y8uFLtLcHk8?si=g_ZYzqzjhuzewZBI\"},{\"title\":\"Lena Lake Backpacking and Hammock. Olympic Peninsula, Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/GnEQwr5TD4M?si=X_bvsCDXpNeEyN-X\"}]'),
(38, 'Loup Loup Ski Bowl', 'Located in the Okanogan Highlands, Loup Loup Ski Bowl is a winter haven for skiing and snowboarding enthusiasts. Known for its family-friendly atmosphere, the ski bowl offers a range of slopes suitable for all skill levels. Beyond winter activities, the area transforms into a scenic landscape for hiking and mountain biking during the summer months.', '97 FS, 4200 100 Road, Okanogan, WA 98840', 'Phone: (509) 557-3401\nEmail: info@skitheloup.com', 'Fri-Sun: 9 AM - 5 PM\nClosed Mon-Thur', 'Varies from Free - $70', '[{\"url\":\"https://skitheloup.com/wp-content/uploads/loup-loup-ski-bowl-view-from-the-base.jpg\",\"src\":\"Loup Loup Ski Bowl\"},{\"url\":\"https://ontherichterscale.files.wordpress.com/2015/02/p1280816.jpg?w=2000&h=1500&crop=1\",\"src\":\"On the Richter Scale\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Loup Loup Ski Bowl | Opening Day Highlights {delano productions}\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Id4hCOft8Mk?si=liq-Vs9lKiA1jWwm\"},{\"title\":\"Loup Loup Luge\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/hIvHIvgnoJI?si=q_ZUK5y2wPTwikk-\"}]'),
(39, 'Crystal Mountain Resort', 'A premier destination for outdoor recreation, Crystal Mountain Resort caters to both winter and summer enthusiasts. In winter, the resort offers world-class skiing and snowboarding, while summer welcomes hikers and mountain bikers to explore the scenic trails. The gondola ride provides breathtaking views of Mount Rainier, adding to the resort\'s year-round appeal.', '33914 Crystal Mountain Blvd. Crystal Mountain, WA 98022', 'Phone: 833-279-7895\nEmail: gservice@skicrystal.com', 'Closed until Winter 23/24', 'Varies by day and type of pass', '[{\"url\":\"https://149799271.v2.pressablecdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/05/Mt-Rainier-Gondola-courtesy-Crystal-Mountain-240DPI.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Rainier\"},{\"url\":\"https://cdn.skimag.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/ski1018-rg-crystal.jpg\",\"src\":\"Ski Magazine\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Crystal Mountain - Washington\'s Largest Ski Resort\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/nffSVclgLHM?si=5O5Q9h_Q4CWNHhAf\"},{\"title\":\"Crystal Mountain 22/23 Season Recap\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qpCyLbP3rVw?si=NIKIjhmAzkeWSkQV\"},{\"title\":\"POW CITY // My favorite POV clips from Crystal Mountain 2023 \",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BfQ1rzmDdsY?si=v617pjt7Zx2ef-IO\"},{\"title\":\"This Is Winter at Crystal Mountain \",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/zK5eucnNGtY?si=QQQJeRQlFblo78pG\"}]'),
(40, 'Stevens Pass', 'A gateway to the Central Cascades, Stevens Pass is a year-round destination for outdoor activities. In winter, it transforms into a popular ski resort, while the summer months welcome hikers and mountain bikers. The Pacific Crest Trail intersects the pass, providing a scenic backdrop for adventurers exploring this dynamic alpine environment.', '93001 NE Stevens Pass Hwy, US 2, Skykomish, WA 98288', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367', 'Mon-Tue: 9 AM - 4 PM\nWed-Sun: 9 AM - 10 PM', 'Varies by day and type of pass', '[{\"url\":\"https://scene7.vailresorts.com/is/image/vailresorts/02-4?resMode=sharp2&wid=412&fit=constrain,1&dpr=on,2.625\",\"src\":\"Snow\"},{\"url\":\"https://res.cloudinary.com/sagacity/image/upload/c_crop,h_3000,w_4500,x_0,y_0/c_limit,dpr_auto,f_auto,fl_lossy,q_80,w_1200/SouthernCross-Courtesy-of-Stevens-Pass_RGB_wlafy9.jpg\",\"src\":\"Seattle Met\"},{\"url\":\"https://snowbrains.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/about-sp-ft1.jpeg\",\"src\":\"SnowBrains\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Skiing, Exploring New Lines at Stevens Pass - Sunday Sendies #6, 12-31-2022\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/bxA5Z8FaRpk?si=q_PpNz_ch8m922mZ\"},{\"title\":\"Epic Powder Snowboarding in the Pacific North West\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/vI6wGdcAX14?si=j2VoFYo3G4KMCQaO\"},{\"title\":\"STEVENS PASS PARK SKIING \\\"KOSHER\\\"\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/wMKNTP6NnFk?si=garfvDKoHMGQbbAf\"}]'),
(41, 'Puget Sound', 'Embracing the coastline of Washington, Puget Sound is a complex and vibrant marine ecosystem. Its shores are dotted with charming towns, offering opportunities for whale watching, kayaking, and exploring marine life. Ferries crisscross the sound, providing picturesque views of the surrounding mountains and islands.', 'Puget Sound, WA', '   ', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.panpacificseattle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/04/Puget-Sound-Wildlife-1024x680.jpg?x58814\",\"src\":\"Pan Pacific Seattle\"},{\"url\":\"https://lakehomes.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/puget-sound-Walt-Kochan-washingtonnature.jpg\",\"src\":\"Lake Homes Realty\"},{\"url\":\"https://media-hofftoseetheworld.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/01/26111249/Puget-Sound-Islands-1024x691.jpg\",\"src\":\"Hoff To See The World\"},{\"url\":\"https://a-z-animals.com/media/2023/07/shutterstock-624389360-huge-licensed-scaled-1024x683.jpg\",\"src\":\"A-Z Animals\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Geology of Seattle and the Puget Sound\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oSSxdogrv1s?si=Uw4E6VXQW3ftP1dW\"},{\"title\":\"OLYMPIA WASHINGTON - EXPLORING THE PUGET SOUND - TRAVEL VLOG\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-h7Z2yX-aEo?si=vBHtgaoJekTBcb2Y\"},{\"title\":\"Cruising South Puget Sound to Jarrell Cove, WA [NORDHAVN 43]\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/mDEJOURM8tU?si=oZ5mKejOJ13NCTVq\"}]'),
(42, 'Lake Chelan', 'Nestled amidst the North Cascades, Lake Chelan is a pristine glacial lake offering a variety of recreational opportunities. With crystal-clear waters, the lake invites boating, fishing, and swimming during the summer. The surrounding vineyards add a touch of sophistication, making the area a delightful year-round destination.', 'Lake Chelan, WA', 'Phone: 509.682.3503\nEmail: info@lakechelan.com', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://www.visitchelancounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/Hiking-Trails-Lake-Chelan.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Chelan County\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.visitchelancounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/01/lake-chelan-wintertime-.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Chelan County\"},{\"url\":\"https://lakechelannow.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/jerry1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Lake Chelan County\"},{\"url\":\"https://a.travel-assets.com/findyours-php/viewfinder/images/res70/151000/151867-Chelan.jpg\",\"src\":\"Expedia\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Lake Chelan Geology\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I3ecBxsW2Mo?si=Y1MLdAodWK-7yhpf\"},{\"title\":\"What to do in Lake Chelan | Local Lens Seattle\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/mrmczYiMWas?si=pTZ3d4jqNzCYSR7L\"},{\"title\":\"Lake Chelan WA | Places to see in Washington State\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/nesGRXrRZb8?si=8D8iz5Rfyb6EsBF-\"}]'),
(43, 'San Juan Islands', 'Sprinkled like gems in the waters of Puget Sound, the San Juan Islands form a serene archipelago that beckons with natural beauty and tranquility. Each island, from Orcas to Friday Harbor, is a unique tapestry of landscapes, offering visitors a diverse range of experiences. Explore charming island communities, witness breathtaking coastal vistas, and engage in outdoor activities like kayaking and whale watching. The San Juan Islands embody the essence of the Pacific Northwest, inviting travelers to unwind in a picturesque blend of island life and pristine nature.', 'San Juan Islands, WA', 'Phone: 888-468-3701', '24 hours', 'Fare for the ferry ride vary', '[{\"url\":\"https://sanjuan.objects.liquidweb.services/photos/20-san-juan-islands-aerial-2800x900.jpg\",\"src\":\"San Juan Islands\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.visittheusa.com/sites/default/files/styles/hero_l/public/images/hero_media_image/2016-10/Lime%20Kiln%20Point%20Lighthouse%2C%20San%20Juan%20Island%2C%20WA2_0.jpg?h=8f6a6b7f&itok=nwy_QoQK\",\"src\":\"Visit The USA\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.valisemag.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Things-to-Do-on-San-Juan-Island-Hero.png\",\"src\":\"Valerie and Valise\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.explorersue.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/San-Juan-Whales-Cover.jpg\",\"src\":\"Explorer Sue\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"San Juan Islands - A road trip around San Juan Island and Orcas Island\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/y0S82-2Z3MI?si=wDVZwdr6b7ZkwXjk\"},{\"title\":\"The Best Things to Do on San Juan Island in Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/JViuU9TB66Y?si=Sh4lRvRfXwbLxQs7\"},{\"title\":\"Top Things to do on San Juan Island | Washington\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/DbGuBl3dm_M?si=WblefHdU1RAWhIWN\"}]'),
(44, 'Leavenworth Ziplines', 'Nestled in the scenic Cascades, Leavenworth Ziplines combines the thrill of adventure with breathtaking natural beauty. This high-flying experience lets visitors soar through the treetops, enjoying panoramic views of the surrounding wilderness. The ziplines offer an adrenaline-pumping journey above lush forests, providing an exhilarating perspective on the Cascade Mountains. Beyond the thrill, Leavenworth Ziplines creates an unforgettable fusion of adventure and the pristine landscapes of the Pacific Northwest.', '19115 Chiwawa Loop Rd. Leavenworth, WA 98826', 'Phone: (206) 625-1367\nEmail: ziplines@mtsprings.com', 'Temporarily closed', '$89-$139', '[{\"url\":\"https://dynamic-media-cdn.tripadvisor.com/media/photo-o/2a/38/7f/a2/hang-out-with-us-in-the.jpg?w=1200&h=900&s=1\",\"src\":\"Tripadvisor\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.visitchelancounty.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/Leavenworth_Zip_Lines_platform_in_trees_leavenworth_wa.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Chelan County\"},{\"url\":\"https://pbs.twimg.com/media/DjiCq8JV4AADbhQ.jpg\",\"src\":\"X\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Leavenworth Zip Lines - High Flying Adventure in Washington State!\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/VFi6klWVQSg?si=0q3XF61p9qvs-lo1\"},{\"title\":\"Leavenworth Ziplines\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OTDXWVd9dE0?si=O3RZBTCiRS8t4KSN\"},{\"title\":\"Leavenworth Zipline Adventure\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HQW4kpaH3ic?si=BWwbwApLKVWVumAx\"}]'),
(45, 'The Summit at Snoqualmie', 'Tucked within the breathtaking Cascade Range, The Summit at Snoqualmie is a year-round haven for outdoor enthusiasts. In the winter, it transforms into a winter sports paradise with four distinct base areas, offering a variety of terrain for skiing and snowboarding. As the snow melts, the mountains come alive with hiking and mountain biking trails, scenic chairlift rides, and panoramic views of the surrounding alpine landscape. The Summit provides not only exhilarating adventures but also a serene escape into the natural beauty of the Cascades.', '1001 WA-906, Snoqualmie Pass, WA 98068', 'Phone: (425) 434-7669', 'Temporarily closed', 'Varies by day and type of pass', '[{\"url\":\"https://skiliftblog.files.wordpress.com/2015/09/img_3932.jpg\",\"src\":\"Lift Blog\"},{\"url\":\"https://cdn.sanity.io/images/bjsgnxuy/production/94e1f3f1ae1040eb9a6e4cf01c4bea4dd2a6193d-1920x1080.jpg?rect=376,0,1168,1080&w=768&h=710&q=65&auto=format\",\"src\":\"Ikon Pass\"},{\"url\":\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fd6e6b922-fd7e-4b87-ba3a-da182f0949e9_2000x1333.jpeg\",\"src\":\"The Storm Skiing Journal and Podcast\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Snowboarding at Summit at Snoqualmie in Washington! #snowboard\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/VIpGxlxD_DQ?si=tp7S2D4qdSvsgBS1\"},{\"title\":\"Snowboarding at The Summit at Snoqualmie! (Winter 22/23)\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/KxKMbg22IXw?si=bKDA-gzysKYu5Kuz\"},{\"title\":\"2022-23 Season Highlights\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/xr34S8hFufw?si=_kHOmmb4txDCuFfJ\"}]'),
(46, 'Space Needle', 'Towering above the Seattle skyline, the Space Needle is an iconic symbol of the city\'s innovation and modernity. Beyond its architectural significance, the Space Needle offers a captivating experience for visitors. The observation deck, with its floor-to-ceiling glass windows, provides a 360-degree panoramic view of Seattle, Puget Sound, and the distant mountains. The Space Needle\'s design, complete with rotating glass floors and interactive exhibits, ensures that every visit is an immersive journey into the heart of Seattle\'s history, culture, and stunning vistas.', '400 Broad St, Seattle, WA 98109', 'Phone: (206) 905-2100', 'Varies by date', 'General Admission: $26-$39', '[{\"url\":\"https://insightpestnorthwest.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/andrea-leopardi-QfhbK2pY0Ao-unsplash-1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Insight Pest Solutions\"},{\"url\":\"https://media.cntraveler.com/photos/5b4e1678b6801415eae751e8/1:1/w_2587,h_2587,c_limit/Space-Needle_John-Lok_2018_7M7A8665.jpg\",\"src\":\"Conde Nast Traveler\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.adsttc.com/media/images/5da8/7bb1/3312/fd27/1100/0200/newsletter/13049_00_N850_high.jpg?1571322788\",\"src\":\"ArchDaily\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.architecturalrecord.com/ext/resources/news/2018/08-August/Renovated-Space-Needle/Space-Needle-2018-Nic-Lehoux-Seattle-01.jpg\",\"src\":\"Architectural Record\"},{\"url\":\"https://image-tc.galaxy.tf/wijpeg-af9gs371gwzp0k24znxbsbl5r/cgh-poi-seattle-space-needle_wide.jpg?crop=89%2C0%2C1742%2C980&width=1280\",\"src\":\"Coast Hotels\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"What\'s inside the Space Needle?\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/y0hsl8C7kZw?si=8VYINwAfai7XYmKO\"},{\"title\":\"Seattle\'s Space Needle gets $100M+ makeover\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/HLegXStUfBo?si=iKN82TM3tOtnwykm\"},{\"title\":\"Seattle Space Needle Observation Deck\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/t1wGabBTcgw?si=G4iR6WXvNa5vlJlx\"}]'),
(47, 'Skyline Tower', 'Gracefully dominating the Bellevue skyline, Skyline Tower stands as a contemporary architectural marvel and a residential gem. This high-rise not only offers luxurious living spaces but also provides its residents with sweeping views of the surrounding urban landscape. Situated in downtown Bellevue, Skyline Tower is more than a residence; it\'s a modern hub that seamlessly integrates convenience with sophistication, placing its residents at the epicenter of the city\'s vibrant energy and cultural offerings.', '10900 NE 4th St, Bellevue, WA 98004', 'Phone: (425) 635-2310', 'Mon-Fri: 7 am – 6 pm', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://images1.loopnet.com/i2/LVvgTLsqqtRBAT1jWNF4muhjCDsRDwqXgskkTNfByIk/110/10900-NE-4th-St-Bellevue-WA-Building-Photo-1-Large.jpg\",\"src\":\"LoopNet\"},{\"url\":\"https://kilroyrealty.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/01_Skyline-scaled.jpg\",\"src\":\"Kilroy Realty\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Regus - Bellevue Skyline Tower - Center Tour\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/oYHZbFt5i4k?si=S_5yi0ZodwgxBVTS\"}]'),
(48, 'Columbia Center', 'Piercing the sky as Seattle\'s tallest skyscraper, the Columbia Center is a defining feature of the city\'s skyline. Beyond its towering presence, the Columbia Center houses a dynamic blend of offices, restaurants, and amenities. The Sky View Observatory, perched atop the skyscraper, invites visitors to experience unparalleled views of Seattle and its surroundings. From the bustling urban life below to the distant peaks of the Cascade Mountains, the Columbia Center offers a unique perspective on the vibrant tapestry of the Pacific Northwest.', '701 5th Ave, Seattle, WA 98104', 'Phone: (206) 386-5151', 'Mon-Sat: 10 AM - 8 PM\nSun: 11 AM - 7 PM', '$20-$38 for Sky View Observatory', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/e/e0/Columbia_center_from_smith_tower.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://columbiacenterseattle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/504-1024x1002.jpg\",\"src\":\"Columbia Center Seattle\"},{\"url\":\"https://gawcapital.s3.ap-southeast-1.amazonaws.com/media/wp-content/uploads/2021/04/20b2c0a52b5fb5cabd3e8480a021b4b6.jpeg\",\"src\":\"Gaw Capital Partners\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.seattletimes.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/b9800166-6f55-11e8-ad2b-6fe209a17856.jpg?d=780x492\",\"src\":\"The Seattle Times\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"4K Walking Tour: Sky View Observatory - Columbia Center in Seattle, WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/if1X4njS-Eo?si=AdN6bvU5FYvOtgq-\"},{\"title\":\"COLUMBIA CENTER, SEATTLE\'s Tallest Building | jeanVLOG\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/QJ_EX1QPg7A?si=e29xesMH94g_Ynbp\"},{\"title\":\"Seattle Trip | Sky View Observatory | Columbia Center | Starbucks reserve roastery\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/BndxCuC965U?si=23bssTMINnUCfKIf\"}]'),
(49, 'Pike Place Market', 'Pike Place Market, a bustling and historic landmark nestled in the heart of Seattle, is a sensory feast for locals and visitors alike. Beyond its role as a market, Pike Place is a vibrant community hub, showcasing the Pacific Northwest\'s rich offerings. From fresh produce to local crafts and artisanal products, the market exudes a lively charm. Witness the iconic fish throwing at Pike Place Fish Market, explore the diverse stalls, and savor the essence of the region through the myriad flavors, sights, and sounds that make Pike Place Market a quintessential Seattle experience.', '1531 Western Ave, Seattle, WA 98101', 'Phone: (206) 682-7453', '10 AM - 5 PM', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/6a/Pike_Place_Market_Seattle.jpg\",\"src\":\"Wikipedia\"},{\"url\":\"https://images.axios.com/c8AUyWd_Nzd0wXSiFlddf3VKaqY=/380x0:1820x1080/1920x1440/2023/10/11/1697058848331.png\",\"src\":\"Axios\"},{\"url\":\"https://a.cdn-hotels.com/gdcs/production199/d929/54c3a599-cb65-4600-99e5-769392159e96.jpg\",\"src\":\"Hotels\"},{\"url\":\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cSIatB5E6KKkf_fmJsXeArwpiZg=/0x78:4000x2172/fit-in/1200x630/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_asset/file/11280599/Pike_Place_Market_Entrance.0.0.0.jpg\",\"src\":\"Eater Seattle\"},{\"url\":\"https://uploads.visitseattle.org/2015/04/17020329/PikePlaceFish_creditChrisBachmann.jpg\",\"src\":\"Visit Seattle\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.tripsavvy.com/thmb/bZpTdUBuldxskm_51JpswK2BWdw=/5472x3648/filters:no_upscale():max_bytes(150000):strip_icc()/6B3A4425-5bfefa3046e0fb00513cf5a5.jpg\",\"src\":\"TripSavvy\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Pike Place Market Visitor Guide - What to See, Do, and Eat\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/Zb7U7BWL-Eo?si=SkdJZuwU2ZFC-Eq8\"},{\"title\":\"Keith Eats Everything At Pike Place Market\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/6TZye-behRA?si=DLaETP1sVf9r26Ou\"},{\"title\":\"Pike Place Market - AMERICA\'S #1 CHOWDER + Must-Eat Market Tour in Seattle | American Food!\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/TvfePq94NUg?si=IZMsgG3k3bmIbBKW\"},{\"title\":\"Flying Fish throwing attraction at Pike Place Market in Seattle, WA\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/fiWLGLl_kpk?si=lkd-1A5F6KiWK01I\"}]'),
(50, 'Leavenworth', 'Tucked into the foothills of the Cascades, Leavenworth is a charming Bavarian-inspired village that captivates with its unique character and alpine ambiance. Beyond its architectural charm, the village offers a rich tapestry of cultural experiences, from authentic German cuisine to traditional festivals. Explore the cobblestone streets lined with boutique shops, savor local delicacies, and immerse yourself in the festive atmosphere, especially during events like Oktoberfest. Leavenworth is not just a destination; it\'s a delightful escape into a European-inspired haven amid the beauty of the Cascade Mountains.', 'Leavenworth, WA', 'Phone: (509) 670-0121', '24 hours', 'Free', '[{\"url\":\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/qbuJdrCnRAFhV9zaxQm1UG-gOA0=/0x0:1800x1350/1200x900/filters:focal(756x531:1044x819)/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70098427/11206610_10153428570276833_6005072325537841179_o.0.0.0.0.jpg\",\"src\":\"Destination Leavenworth\"},{\"url\":\"https://2traveldads.com/wp-content/uploads/Taylor-Family-with-Bavarian-Buildings-in-Leavenworth-Washington-2.jpg\",\"src\":\"2TravelDads\"},{\"url\":\"https://2traveldads.com/wp-content/uploads/Bavarian-Buildings-in-Leavenworth-Washington-1.jpg\",\"src\":\"2TravelDads\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.twowanderingsoles.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/img_60ee8f5e4c47a.jpg\",\"src\":\"Two Wandering Soles\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.discoverthepnw.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/11/Leavenworth-at-night-aerial-from-Chamber-of-Commerce.jpg\",\"src\":\"Discover the Pacific Northwest\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Leavenworth: Your Winter Wonderland\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/FTyVydTNRqI?si=oQ8lPZqku8kBnxHt\"},{\"title\":\"Leavenworth Christmas lights\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/OM0dL2BmOeU?si=GXJtuNI9GuorHvDc\"},{\"title\":\"Leavenworth, Washington - The Ultimate Winter Wonderland 4K Walking Tour 2019\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/E05yigqLu4Q?si=Ng59WbZhtMahbBIH\"}]'),
(51, 'Wild Waves Theme and Water Park', 'Wild Waves Theme and Water Park, located in Federal Way, provides a thrilling fusion of amusement park excitement and water-based adventures. The park boasts a diverse range of rides, from adrenaline-pumping roller coasters to refreshing water slides. Families and thrill-seekers alike can enjoy a day of excitement, laughter, and relaxation. Beyond the rides, the park hosts seasonal events, live entertainment, and a vibrant atmosphere that makes Wild Waves a go-to destination for summertime fun in the Pacific Northwest.', '36201 Enchanted Pkwy S, Federal Way, WA 98003', 'Phone: (253) 661-8000', 'Temporarily closed', '$34-$120', '[{\"url\":\"https://images.seattleschild.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/07/Wild-Waves-3-scaled-e1689831858537.jpg\",\"src\":\"Seattle\'s Child\"},{\"url\":\"https://tinybeans.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/wild-waves-theme-water-park-hooks-lagoon.jpg\",\"src\":\"Tinybeans\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.federalwaymirror.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/web1_161118-FWM-WildWaves_2.jpg\",\"src\":\"Federal Way Mirror\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.kentreporter.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/05/25250428_web1_WildWaves-FWM-210521-tsr_1.jpg\",\"src\":\"Kent Reporter\"},{\"url\":\"https://patch.com/img/cdn/users/20457122/2013/05/raw/4dd75324cc4d49da35f8a994c1ab6b34.png\",\"src\":\"Patch\"}]', '[{\"title\":\"Wild Waves Theme & Water Park Tour & Review with The Legend\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/IV-vAQVbysk?si=CO1SFg-AISeNpdT0\"},{\"title\":\"Wild Waves Theme & Water Park - 2023\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/o4acwWknNRg?si=EBVVT_qQZp9rl4Zs\"},{\"title\":\"Visiting WILD WAVES, Washington\'s Biggest (& ONLY!) Theme Park\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/V8Cjr3sfNAk?si=qsCMatHOn9F6Pkzn\"}]'),
(59, 'Olympic Park', 'Encompassing a staggering diversity of ecosystems, Olympic National Park is a natural wonderland that showcases the breadth of nature\'s beauty. From the lush Hoh Rainforest to the alpine peaks of the Olympic Mountains, the park offers an immersive experience for outdoor enthusiasts. Explore the pristine coastline, venture into old-growth forests, and embark on challenging hikes. Notable events include ranger-led programs, providing insights into the park\'s rich biodiversity, Native American history, and the ever-changing landscapes.', '3002 Mt Angeles Rd, Port Angeles, WA 98362', 'Phone: (360) 565-3130', '24 hours', 'Entrance Pass ($15.00-$30.00) required for all visitors', '[object Object]', '');
INSERT INTO `attractions` (`id`, `name`, `category`, `subcategory`, `description`, `location`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `must_visit`, `hidden_gem`) VALUES
(1, 'Olympic National Park', 'Natural', 'Landscapes', 'Olympic National Park is on Washington\'s Olympic Peninsula in the Pacific Northwest. The park sprawls across several different ecosystems from the dramatic peaks of the Olympic Mountains to old-growth forests. The summit of glacier-clad Mt. Olympus is popular with climbers, and hiking and backpacking trails cut through the park\'s rainforests and along its Pacific coastline', 'Port Angeles', 47.969350, -123.498560, 1, 0),
(2, 'Mount Rainier National Park', 'Natural', 'Landscapes', 'Nestled in the Cascade Range, Mount Rainier National Park is home to the iconic Mount Rainier, an active stratovolcano and the highest peak in the state. Visitors can explore subalpine meadows, dense forests, and glaciers, as well as enjoy activities like hiking, wildlife watching, and snow sports depending on the season.', 'Ashford', 46.850000, -121.750000, 1, 0),
(3, 'Hoh Rainforest', 'Natural', 'Landscapes', 'One of the largest temperate rainforests in the U.S. Famous for its lush greenery, towering moss-draped trees, and diverse plant and animal life, the Hoh Rainforest offers visitors the chance to experience a unique ecosystem and enjoy hiking trails that wind through its enchanting landscape.', 'Forks', 47.861444, -123.924667, 1, 0),
(4, 'Steptoe Butte State Park', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'Rising above the Palouse Hills, Steptoe Butte State Park offers panoramic views of the surrounding agricultural landscapes. This iconic butte is a popular spot for photography, especially during sunrise and sunset, when the rolling hills are bathed in warm, golden light.', 'Colfax', 47.032500, -117.298611, 0, 1),
(5, 'Deception Pass State Park', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'Deception Pass State Park is located on Whidbey Island and offers a diverse range of outdoor activities. Visitors can explore scenic trails, admire the breathtaking views from the iconic Deception Pass Bridge, and engage in water activities such as kayaking and beachcombing.', 'Oak Harbor', 48.406389, -122.644444, 1, 0),
(6, 'North Cascades National Park', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'A vast wilderness of conifer-clad mountains, glaciers and lakes. The North Cascades Highway passes viewpoints and leads to trails such as the steep Thunder Creek Trail. ', 'Sedro-Woolley', 48.832778, -121.347500, 1, 0),
(7, 'Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument is a U.S. National Monument that includes the area around Mount St. Helens in Washington. Visitors can explore the blast zone, witness the recovering landscape, and learn about the geological processes that shaped the area through interpretive centers and hiking trails.', 'Castle Rock', 46.233166, -122.184541, 1, 0),
(8, 'Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'Encompassing a vast expanse of wilderness, the Mount Baker-Snoqualmie National Forest includes the towering Mount Baker and diverse ecosystems. Outdoor enthusiasts can enjoy activities such as hiking, skiing, and camping while surrounded by pristine forests, alpine meadows, and mountainous terrain.', 'Marblemount', 47.766000, -121.378000, 0, 0),
(9, 'Lake Wenatchee State Park', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'Set on the shores of Lake Wenatchee, this state park offers a range of recreational activities. Visitors can enjoy boating, fishing, camping, and hiking in the picturesque surroundings of the lake and surrounding forested areas.', 'Leavenworth', 47.811389, -120.727778, 0, 1),
(10, 'Grove of the Patriarchs', 'Natural', 'Parks and Reserves', 'A serene forested area featuring ancient and towering trees. Visitors can explore a loop trail that crosses the Ohanapecosh River via a suspension bridge, providing an up-close encounter with some of the oldest and largest trees in the region.', 'Packwood', 46.800373, -121.555652, 0, 1),
(11, 'Ruby Beach', 'Natural', 'Beaches', 'Renowned for its scenic beauty and unique sea stacks. Visitors can explore tide pools, take in stunning views of the rugged coastline, and enjoy the dramatic sunsets that paint the sky with vibrant colors.', 'Jefferson County', 47.710833, -124.415556, 0, 0),
(12, 'Long Beach', 'Natural', 'Beaches', 'Known as the \"World\'s Longest Beach.\" It offers visitors opportunities for beachcombing, kite flying, and enjoying the coastal scenery. The nearby town of Long Beach provides a charming seaside experience.', 'Long Beach', 46.350833, -124.053611, 0, 0),
(13, 'Second Beach', 'Natural', 'Beaches', 'Camping & hiking draw visitors to this breathtaking beach with sea stacks, eagles & whale sightings', 'Port Angeles', 47.885523, -124.620529, 0, 0),
(14, 'Shi Shi Beach', 'Natural', 'Beaches', 'Part of Olympic National Park, this coastline features a trail leading to beach & forest campsites.', 'Clallam Bay', 48.262023, -124.683086, 0, 1),
(15, 'Wallace Falls', 'Natural', 'Waterfalls', 'Wallace Falls State Park is home to a stunning series of cascading waterfalls, with the main attraction being Wallace Falls. Hikers can follow a trail that passes by multiple viewpoints, offering varying perspectives of these picturesque waterfalls set against a backdrop of lush greenery.', 'Gold Bar', 47.870556, -121.653889, 0, 1),
(16, 'Nooksack Falls', 'Natural', 'Waterfalls', 'A waterfall along the North Fork of the Nooksack River in Whatcom County, Washington. The water flows through a narrow valley and drops freely 88 feet into a deep rocky river canyon. The falls are viewable from the forested cover near the cliffs edge', 'Glacier', 48.905278, -121.808889, 0, 1),
(17, 'Snoqualmie Falls', 'Natural', 'Waterfalls', 'A powerful and iconic waterfall on the Snoqualmie River. Easily accessible from the town of Snoqualmie, visitors can enjoy viewpoints overlooking the falls and explore the nearby park area. The falls are particularly scenic during different seasons.', 'Snoqualmie', 47.541500, -121.837300, 1, 0),
(18, 'Palouse Falls State Park', 'Natural', 'Waterfalls', 'Basalt canyons & a 198-ft. thundering waterfall with an ADA-accessible overlook, plus a campground.', 'LaCrosse', 46.663611, -118.223611, 0, 1),
(19, 'Franklin Falls', 'Natural', 'Waterfalls', 'Franklin Falls is a waterfall on the South fork of the Snoqualmie River, the first of three major waterfalls on the South Fork Snoqualmie River. A short hike through the forest leads to this beautiful cascade, making it a favorite destination for hikers and nature enthusiasts.', 'Snoqualmie', 47.424970, -121.432430, 0, 1),
(20, 'Guler Ice Caves', 'Natural', 'Caves', 'These ice caves, formed by melting glacial ice, offer a unique and chilly adventure for those willing to explore their icy chambers.', 'Trout Lake', 45.961510, -121.632949, 0, 1),
(21, 'Ape Cave', 'Natural', 'Caves', 'Ape Cave is a lava tube cave in the Mount St. Helens National Volcanic Monument. Visitors can explore the subterranean environment, navigating through the dark passages and marveling at the unique geological formations left behind by volcanic activity.', 'Amboy', 46.110147, -122.211518, 0, 0),
(22, 'Chihuly Garden and Glass', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Museums', 'Chihuly Garden and Glass is an exhibit in the Seattle Center directly next to the Space Needle, showcasing the studio glass of Dale Chihuly.', 'Seattle', 47.620620, -122.350070, 1, 0),
(23, 'Musuem of Pop Culture (MoPOP)', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Museums', 'Located in Seattle, the Museum of Pop Culture celebrates popular culture in all its forms. Exhibits cover music, science fiction, video games, and more. The iconic building, designed by Frank Gehry, is a work of art in itself.', 'Seattle', 47.621500, -122.348600, 1, 0),
(24, 'Washington State History Museum', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Museums', 'Situated in Tacoma, the Washington State History Museum showcases the diverse history of the state through engaging exhibits and artifacts. Visitors can explore exhibits ranging from Native American heritage to the modern era.', 'Tacoma', 47.245000, -122.436111, 0, 0),
(25, 'The Museum of Flight', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Museums', 'Based in Seattle, The Museum of Flight is one of the largest air and space museums in the world. It features a vast collection of aircraft, spacecraft, and aviation-related artifacts, providing a comprehensive look at the history of flight.', 'Seattle', 47.518000, -122.297000, 1, 0),
(26, 'Bainbridge Island Museum of Art', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Museums', 'Overlooking Puget Sound, the Bainbridge Island Museum of Art features contemporary artwork from regional artists. The museum is committed to promoting the understanding and appreciation of the arts.', 'Bainbridge Island', 47.625100, -122.514500, 0, 1),
(27, 'Fort Vancouver National Historic Site', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Historical Sites', 'This historic site preserves the legacy of Fort Vancouver, a 19th-century fur trading post. Visitors can explore reconstructed buildings, engage in living history demonstrations, and learn about the region\'s colonial history.', 'Vancouver', 45.625395, -122.658153, 0, 0),
(28, 'Pioneer Square', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Historical Sites', 'Art galleries, coffee shops and trendy bars fill Pioneer Square’s late-1800s Romanesque Revival buildings. Tourists explore subterranean streets on the guided Underground Tour, and learn about Seattle’s roots at the Klondike Gold Rush National Historical Park. ', 'Seattle', 47.601667, -122.331944, 0, 0),
(29, 'Fort Casey State Park', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Historical Sites', 'Fort Casey State Park is a 467-acre marine camping park with a lighthouse and sweeping views of Admiralty Inlet and the Strait of Juan de Fuca. A coast artillery post features two 10-inch and two 3-inch historic guns on display. The park features 10,810 feet of saltwater shoreline on Puget Sound Admiralty Inlet.', 'Coupeville', 48.164167, -122.678889, 0, 0),
(30, 'Manresa Castle', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Historical Sites', 'A historic hotel with a captivating past. Built as a private residence, it has served various purposes over the years and is known for its distinctive architecture and reportedly haunted reputation.', 'Port Townsend', 48.104935, -122.789837, 0, 1),
(31, 'Roslyn Historic District', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Historical Sites', 'A charming town with well-preserved buildings from the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Known for its mining history, it gained fame as the filming location for the TV series \"Northern Exposure.\"', 'Rosyln', 47.225000, -121.003056, 0, 1),
(32, 'Marmes Rockshelter', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Archaeological Sites', 'The Marmes Rockshelter is an archaeological site first excavated in 1962. The site offers a glimpse into the prehistoric lifestyle of Native American communities.', 'Franklin County', 46.614310, -118.202420, 0, 1),
(33, 'Hanford Reach National Monument', 'Cultural and Historical', 'Archaeological Sites', 'Known for its natural beauty, diverse wildlife, and cultural significance. It also includes the last free-flowing, non-tidal section of the Columbia River in the United States.', 'Mattawa', 46.583333, -119.516667, 0, 1),
(34, 'The Enchantments', 'Adventure', 'Hiking and Trekking', ' A stunning alpine wilderness area in the Cascade Range, known for its pristine lakes, jagged peaks, and vibrant larch trees in the fall. Accessible through a permit system, it\'s a favorite destination for hikers and backpackers seeking a backcountry experience.', 'Leavenworth', 47.481111, -120.803889, 0, 1),
(35, 'Mount Si', 'Adventure', 'Hiking and Trekking', 'A popular hiking destination offering panoramic views of the surrounding landscapes, including the Puget Sound and Mount Rainier. The challenging trail is well-loved by locals and visitors alike.', 'North Bend', 47.507603, -121.740109, 1, 0),
(36, 'Rattlesnake Ledge', 'Adventure', 'Hiking and Trekking', 'Rattlesnake Ledge, part of the Rattlesnake Mountain trail system, is a rewarding hike near North Bend. The trail leads to a viewpoint overlooking Rattlesnake Lake and the surrounding mountains, providing a relatively short but scenic outdoor experience.', 'North Bend', 47.458436, -121.806222, 0, 0),
(37, 'Lena Lake Trail', 'Adventure', 'Hiking and Trekking', 'The Lena Lake Trail, situated in Olympic National Forest, leads to the picturesque Lena Lake. Hikers can enjoy a forested trail along the Hamma Hamma River, eventually reaching the serene lake surrounded by mountains.', 'Lilliwaup', 47.599700, -123.151200, 0, 1),
(38, 'Loup Loup Ski Bowl', 'Adventure', 'Skiing', 'A family-friendly ski area offering winter sports enthusiasts opportunities for skiing, snowboarding, and tubing. The area is known for its welcoming atmosphere and scenic mountain views.', 'Okanogan', 48.394722, -119.912778, 0, 1),
(39, 'Crystal Mountain Resort', 'Adventure', 'Skiing', 'A premier destination for winter sports. In addition to skiing and snowboarding, visitors can take a scenic gondola ride for breathtaking views of the surrounding peaks.', 'Pierce County', 46.928532, -121.504192, 0, 0),
(40, 'Stevens Pass', 'Adventure', 'Skiing', 'A popular mountain pass in the Cascades, known for its ski resort and outdoor recreation opportunities. In winter, it\'s a hub for snow sports, while summer offers hiking, mountain biking, and scenic drives.', 'Skykomish', 47.744722, -121.088889, 0, 0),
(41, 'Puget Sound', 'Adventure', 'Water Sports', 'Puget Sound is a vast inland sea that extends from Olympia to the Canadian border. Known for its diverse marine life, including orcas, and picturesque coastal communities, Puget Sound is a hub for boating, kayaking, and wildlife watching.', 'Puget Sound', 47.600000, -122.400000, 1, 0),
(42, 'Lake Chelan', 'Adventure', 'Water Sports', 'One of the deepest lakes in the United States, is surrounded by vineyards, orchards, and the North Cascades. The lake offers opportunities for water activities, wine tasting, and exploring the charming town of Chelan.', 'Chelan', 47.841111, -120.046389, 0, 0),
(43, 'San Juan Islands', 'Adventure', 'Water Sports', 'A group of islands known for their natural beauty and outdoor recreation. Visitors can enjoy whale watching, kayaking, and exploring charming towns like Friday Harbor.', 'Puget Sound', 48.532066, -123.029251, 1, 0),
(44, 'Leavenworth Ziplines', 'Adventure', 'Adventure Parks', ' An exhilarating adventure through the treetops near the Bavarian-themed town of Leavenworth. The zipline experience provides panoramic views of the surrounding mountains and forests, combining adventure with scenic beauty.', 'Leavenworth', 47.767955, -120.652750, 0, 1),
(45, 'The Summit at Snoqualmie', 'Adventure', 'Adventure Parks', 'A popular ski resort located in the Cascade Range. It offers a variety of winter sports activities, including skiing and snowboarding, making it a favorite destination for outdoor enthusiasts in the Seattle area.', 'Snoqualmie', 47.424000, -121.416000, 0, 0),
(46, 'Space Needle', 'Urban', 'Towers', 'The Space Needle is an observation tower in Seattle. The Space Needle is an iconic landmark in Seattle, known for its futuristic design and panoramic views of the city and surrounding landscapes. ', 'Seattle', 47.620400, -122.349100, 1, 0),
(47, 'Skyline Tower', 'Urban', 'Towers', 'A prominent skyscraper in Bellevue, offering stunning views of the city and beyond. It stands as a symbol of the region\'s modern architecture and is part of Bellevue\'s dynamic urban landscape.', 'Bellevue', 47.614706, -122.193929, 0, 0),
(48, 'Columbia Center', 'Urban', 'Towers', 'The tallest skyscraper in Seattle. The observation deck provides spectacular views of Seattle, Puget Sound, and the Cascade and Olympic mountain ranges, making it a popular destination for locals and tourists alike.', 'Seattle', 47.604530, -122.330690, 0, 0),
(49, 'Pike Place Market', 'Urban', 'Shopping', 'Pike Place Market is a historic public market in Seattle, known for its vibrant atmosphere, fresh produce, local crafts, and the iconic fish-throwing tradition. It\'s a must-visit destination offering a taste of the city\'s culture and culinary delights.', 'Seattle', 47.609444, -122.341667, 1, 0),
(50, 'Leavenworth', 'Urban', 'Shopping', 'Leavenworth is a charming Bavarian-themed town nestled in the Cascade Mountains. Known for its picturesque setting, unique architecture, and festive events, Leavenworth attracts visitors year-round for shopping, dining, and cultural experiences.', 'Leavenworth', 47.596389, -120.665278, 1, 0),
(51, 'Wild Waves Theme and Water Park', 'Urban', 'Amusement Parks', 'A combination of thrilling amusement park rides and refreshing water attractions. It\'s a family-friendly destination, providing fun for visitors of all ages.', 'Federal Way', 47.272500, -122.311500, 0, 0);
